- GDP per capita is a widely used indicator of a country's standard of living; 
- Health expenditure as a percentage of total spending is a key metric to evaluate a country's healthcare system; 
- Ranking these values helps identify which countries have the highest healthcare spending relative to their overall economy.

sql:
SELECT AVG(value) AS avg_expenditure
FROM health_expenditure
WHERE category = 'public';

SELECT MAX(value) AS max_public_expenditure
FROM health_expenditure
WHERE category = 'public';

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_expenditure
FROM health_expenditure
WHERE year = 2020 AND category = 'public';

SELECT category, AVG(value) AS average_expenditure
FROM health_expenditure
GROUP BY category;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS cumulative_reports
FROM reports
WHERE user_id = 0;
